28/01/2008
MELBOURNE, Australia -- Third seed Novak Djokovic of Serbia won the Australian Open final, defeating unseeded Frenchman Jo-Wilfried Tsonga 4-6 6-4 6-3 7-6 on Sunday (January 27th). It was the first grand slam title for Djokovic, 20, and a first for Serbia. (AP, AFP, CNN. B92, Tanjug, Beta - 27/01/08) 
